http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Two-held-for-peddling-ganja/article13992839.ece

A special team of the City police has nabbed two youths for allegedly peddling ganja to students. The accused were identified as Firoz Ibrahim, 21, of Kaloor, and Vipin, 23, of Njarakkal. The sleuths also seized about 2.5 kg of ganja from them.Firoz was held from Thrikkanarvattom at around 9.50 p.m. on Saturday. The police found 1.25 kg of ganja on Firoz. Based on the information provided by Firoz, the police on Sunday nabbed Vipin with 1.25 kg of ganja from Vaduthala.The accused had in their possession small packets of ganja meant to be sold to school and college students in the city.The duo was booked under the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act.They were produced before a magistrate and remanded in judicial custody on Sunday.